 the present or near future, for as Robert had told him, To dwell in the past is to live in regret.', 1190, 0), (20273, 'Don’t be afraid of those failures that do not lead to a loss of life or that do not incapacitate people.', 5111, 0), (20274, '...[R]eal wisdom is the property of God, and... human wisdom has little or no value.', 1595, 0), (20275, 'Love has no color, love has no language and love has no religion.', 5111, 0), (20276, 'When faced with difficulties, a humble, understanding, appreciative and selfless person finds it easy to win a friend. On the other hand, a temperamental, egoistic, condensing, self-absorbed, self-conceited and narrow-minded person who lacks the basic sense of humility easily loses friends when in distress.', 5111, 0), (20277, 'Kindness is a source of relief to the soul of the giver, creating a sense of fortitude that is incomprehensible to those who do not know what kindness is all about.', 5111, 0), (20278, 'There are people who bring joy to our lives, but who fail to make us happy. They are the people for the moment. Never rely on their love because it is not sustainable. Their love is alike a comet that illuminates the sky, but then fades away because it lacks the sustainable energy of the sun.', 5111, 0), (20279, 'We need the wisdom to accept the fact that this world abounds with issues we cannot solve; and we need to part ways with those people, ideas and things that are a vexation to the soul.', 5111, 0), (20280, 'The narrow-minded find it convenient to create stereotypes, and then try to fit everybody, everything and every situation into those stereotypes.', 5111, 0), (20281, 'Some people live their memorable years fighting against their basic instincts only to succumb in the end to what was actually good for them.', 5111, 0), (20282, 'Writers understand the world better, but they lack the strength to change it. Perhaps that is so because they understand their limitations more than others.', 5111, 0), (20283, 'Writers are the most tormented of all the different categories of artists that are out there in the world.', 5111, 0), (20284, 'When singers, actors or artists touch on sorrow, they are trying to give comfort to aggrieved souls by giving some meaning to their sorrows. The job of the singer, actor or artists ,in general, is to make us comfortable with our feelings or emotions―be it pain, hurt, anger, hatred, sadness, pleasure, love, cheerfulness or joy.', 5111, 0), (20285, 'Male writers who never find the stabilizing force of an understanding woman in their lives usually end up as the jaded figures of their days, the types who give much artistic expression to the world, but who are lonely in their overcrowded worlds of love.', 5111, 0), (20286, 'A writer needs a partner who can act as fuel to his artistic mind, yet has the great ability to sober him up and help him be in sync with the non-artistic part of his soul.', 5111, 0), (20287, 'Writers are the most pathetic souls when it comes to expressing their personal feelings. Their personalities are as complex as the characters they have weaved. And in a curious way, without them really knowing it, writers are the sum total of the characters they created in their heads or in their writings. Yes, My Dear Tania; writers are capable of reflecting their characters, even though most of them are determined to be just like your ordinary guy next door.', 5111, 0), (20288, 'We always emerge from the death of a loved one like a phoenix arising from its funeral pyre.', 5111, 0), (20289, 'When somebody you love dies, a phase of life’s innocence dies with that person, and a part of you dies as well.', 5111, 0), (20290, 'Societies and people that come close to being happy are those that do well in narrowing the disparity between their desires and their needs, especially the material things of life.', 5111, 0), (20291, 'In the world of today, human desires far supersede human needs. Waste, as you can see, is the result of all of those contradictions. That is how we ended up complicating our world.', 5111, 0), (20292, '…a writer, like most artists, needs a partner who can act as the fuel to his artistic mind and soul, yet has the great ability to sober him up and help him be in sync with the non-artistic part of his soul.', 5111, 0), (20293, 'In today’s world, human desires far supersede human needs. Waste, as you can see, is the result of that disparity.', 5111, 0), (20294, 'Judgments based on preconceptions make life simple for us to deal with since that means we safely shield ourselves behind barriers of preconception that helped us feel safe in whatever views or assumptions we are having.', 5111, 0), (20295, 'We, humans, have come up with so many superficialities that are completely unnecessary for our existence and happiness on earth.', 5111, 0), (20296, 'Most people have this tendency to make judgments on others based on preconceptions, especially when they are dealing with them for the first time.', 5111, 0), (20297, 'In dealing with others, man is inherently a slave to his preconceptions, to the stereotypes he became familiar with that made life easier for him to comprehend.', 5111, 0), (20298, 'Having a deep sense of understanding is a huge burden for a mind that can’t directly influence things.', 5111, 0), (20299, 'Life is full of intriguing souls that you cannot penetrate… An uncomfortable percentage of those anguished and impregnable souls also have suffering hearts that are further tormented by a deluded mind. They will hurt out of an impulse, and then live their lives after that without the slightest remorse.', 5111, 0), (20300, 'Avoid people who hurt from an impulse. I mean people who have this tendency to relish their capacity to hurt the good souls of this world, and who after hurting, wake up the next day without a trace of despondent brooding, and then move on with life never thinking that they should show some remorse or try to repent.', 5111, 0);
